Docker installation on virtual box

1. Install virtual box
   Download for windows host : https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/6.0.10/VirtualBox-6.0.10-132072-Win.exe


2. Install Linux mint os on virtual box.
   Download : https://linuxmint.com/edition.php?id=263
   
3. Once OS is isnatlled,start the machine, and execute below two command first in the terminal
   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get upgrade
  
4. if encouter with Depackaging(dpkg) error, then run follwing command.
   sudo dpkg --configure -a
   
5. Install docker 
	https://linuxconfig.org/how-to-install-docker-on-ubuntu-18-04-bionic-beaver
  
  sudo apt install docker.io
   
  
   sudo systemctl start docker
   sudo systemctl enable docker
   
6. Verify installation
   docker --version



Useful docker command

1. List of docker images
  - docker images : display all the images
  
2. Check running processes
   docker ps : this will list down only running process
   dcoker ps -a : this will list down all the processes
   
3. stop docker container
   docker stop "container_id"

4. start docker container
   docker stop "container_id"

5. Remove docker container
   docker rm "container_id"

6. Remove docker image
   docker rmi "docker_image_name/tag"


